main event: Radar detected 37 unidentified flying objects over Kincheloe AFB, Michigan, on September 11, 1967, although no visual sightings were made.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 2 hours and 13 minutes, Radar tracked 'blips' at speeds varying between slow to about 2000 mph, The majority of radar detections were explained as probable 'anomalous propagation', A B-52 did not visually observe any of the targets despite being on radar, An investigation was ongoing with UFO researchers from the University of Colorado present at the base.
sighted object: 37 unidentified flying objects (UFOs) detected by radar
witness description: No visual witnesses; the events were solely reported via radar.
